mts.s: The Technology Garden is a great little gem hidden away on the 5th floor of Donald Bren Hall. Since the time when team members of Overkill first discovered its existence last quarter they enjoyed the use of the area to program assignments and write papers while in the company of plants. However many of the plants come and go due to no one really being assigned to their care. Project Overgrowth goal is to bring awareness to the plant conditions by providing updated information on moisture levels. The use of a website will serve to display this information and general information about the room. We fell that bringing a since of awareness to this room may enact a since of responsibility to current students at UCI.
must be available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

Moisture Sensors: A device that can be used on plants and find out what their current moisture level they have. 

Database: A storage area online that takes the data the sensors provide.

Website: Displays information to user of what Project Overgrowth is. It will display what we get from the sensors through the database, turning all that data into valuable information presented in a pleasing manner.

Plant Information: Technology Gardens plant information will be added to the website, which is basically description and status of plants on an individual level. It will include a photo, the name, type of plant and how its doing.

Plant Status: This will use the data retrieved from the database to create charts and alert the users whether the plant needs water, or not.

Television inside the Technology Garden: It must be turned on and connected to internet to display the Project Overgrowth website.
